        <h3>Can you provide tips for maintaining a gas stove?</h3>
        <p>Certainly! Here are some tips for maintaining a gas stove:</p>
        <p>
          1. Clean regularly: Wipe down the stovetop after each use to prevent
          grease and food buildup.
        </p>
        <p>
          2. Check for leaks: Routinely inspect the gas line and connections for
          any signs of leaks, such as hissing sounds or a rotten egg odor.
        </p>
        <p>
          3. Keep burners clean: Remove burner caps and clean them with warm,
          soapy water to ensure proper gas flow.
        </p>
        <p>
          4. Clean the burner ports: Use a small brush or pin to unclog any
          debris from the burner ports to maintain even flames.
        </p>
        <p>
          5. Check the ignition system: Ensure the igniters are sparking
          properly and clean them if necessary to prevent ignition issues.
        </p>
        <p>
          6. Test the flame: Periodically check that the flames are burning
          evenly and adjust the burner caps if needed for optimal heat
          distribution.
